  "technicalDetails": "<p><strong>Features</strong>:</p><ul><li> A fully dynamic ability hotbar that can support - out of the box - up to 9 abilities</li><li> Dynamically add new abilities with interface calls</li><li> Dynamically replace existing abilities with interface calls</li><li>All abilities managed with an Ability Manager, you no longer need to spawn your abilities from your input actions directly</li><li>Input Action Icon dynamic changes between KBM and Xbox Controller (can be easily changed to another gamepad)</li><li>Supporting different ability types! Holding, Charging and Spawning based abilities</li><li>Manual adding of new abilities is as simple as updating a map variable</li><li>Equipped abilities is stored in a single variable, making it incredibly simple to implement in save systems</li></ul><p><strong>Number of Blueprints</strong>: 13 Blueprints (6 of which are for demo purposes and can be deleted if desired), 1 data table, 2 enumerators, a struct and a number of others in the Demo folder (third person character template, demo maps etc.).</p><p><strong>Input</strong>: Keyboard and Mouse &#43; Xbox Gamepad (gamepad is more to do with input action icons, these can be easily changed to another gamepad)</p><p><strong>Network Replicated</strong>: No</p><p><strong>Supported Development Platforms</strong>:</p><p>Windows: Yes</p><p><a href=\"https://nubgamerz.notion.site/EZGAS-Documentation-79a9e57f7042402a8c972029ff6a5bc0\" rel=\"nofollow\">Documentation</a></p><p>Important/Additional Notes:</p><p>This system is a system and not a set of pre-coded abilities. There are plenty of those available on the marketplace. This system allows you to manage those abilities on an ability hotbar, with dynamic adding and updating. You can focus on the ability code, while SGAS does the rest of the integration work for you.</p>",
